to `string` (or `null` in the case of `PASSWORD_DEFAULT`) in PHP 7.4. The [migration guide](https://www.php.net/manual/en/migration74.incompatible.php) states that “applications correctly using [these] will continue to function correctly”. However, this means the signature for `password_hash()` has now changed, with the second argument accepting `string|null` as of PHP 7.4, rather than `int`.\r\n\r\nI'm also seeing an issue when using `PASSWORD_DEFAULT`.\r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR: UndefinedConstant - redacted.php:123:57 - Const PASSWORD_DEFAULT is not defined\r\n            $this->password = \\password_hash($password, \\PASSWORD_DEFAULT);\r\n\r\n\r\nERROR: InvalidArgument - redacted.php:152:51 - Argument 2 of password_hash expects int, string(argon2i) provided\r\n            $password = \\password_hash($password, \\PASSWORD_ARGON2I);\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/2395/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/ps